@wdouglascampbell  the error message is returned as part of rootlessport. 

Can you verify if this behavior exists when running under root?

The check is here: 

```
vendor/github.com/rootless-containers/rootlesskit/pkg/port/portutil/portutil.go

 40 // ValidatePortSpec validates *port.Spec.
 41 // existingPorts can be optionally passed for detecting conflicts.
 42 func ValidatePortSpec(spec port.Spec, existingPorts map[int]*port.Status) error {
 43 ⇥       if spec.Proto != "tcp" && spec.Proto != "udp" {
 44 ⇥       ⇥       return errors.Errorf("unknown proto: %q", spec.Proto)
 45 ⇥       }
 46 ⇥       if spec.ParentIP != "" {
 47 ⇥       ⇥       if net.ParseIP(spec.ParentIP) == nil {
 48 ⇥       ⇥       ⇥       return errors.Errorf("invalid ParentIP: %q", spec.ParentIP)
 49 ⇥       ⇥       }
 50 ⇥       }
 51 ⇥       if spec.ParentPort <= 0 || spec.ParentPort > 65535 {
 52 ⇥       ⇥       return errors.Errorf("invalid ParentPort: %q", spec.ParentPort)
 53 ⇥       }
 54 ⇥       if spec.ChildPort <= 0 || spec.ChildPort > 65535 {
 55 ⇥       ⇥       return errors.Errorf("invalid ChildPort: %q", spec.ChildPort)
 56 ⇥       }
 57 ⇥       for id, p := range existingPorts {
 58 ⇥       ⇥       sp := p.Spec
 59 ⇥       ⇥       sameProto := sp.Proto == spec.Proto
 60 ⇥       ⇥       sameParent := sp.ParentIP == spec.ParentIP && sp.ParentPort == spec.ParentPort
 61 ⇥       ⇥       sameChild := sp.ChildPort == spec.ChildPort
 62 ⇥       ⇥       if sameProto && (sameParent || sameChild) {
 63 ⇥       ⇥       ⇥       return errors.Errorf("conflict with ID %d", id)
 64 ⇥       ⇥       }
 65 ⇥       }
 66 ⇥       return nil
 67 }

```

So I think the check is actually that you're using the same child port - 80 is used twice as a child port, hence your second example - mapping 80 to 80 on one container and 80 to 8080 on another container/IP works.

I can probably test the working state of _not_ using the sameChild spec, but in any case this is a rootlessport problem. 

If you can verify what behavior root has that would help further.
